<h3><font color="blue">Chapter 11</font></h3>
<h1>ATM Concepts</h1>
<hr size=3>
</center>

<h2>
<image src="redball.gif"> <b>ATM</b> stands for <b>A</b>synchronous 
<b>T</b>ransfer <b>M</b>ode <br>
<image src="redball.gif"> Packets have small fixed sizes ,called <i>cells</i><br>
<image src="redball.gif"> Cell has 5 bytes header and payload 48 bytes <br>
<img src="redball.gif"> ATM protocol is designed to minimize processing
overhead <br>
<image src="redball.gif"> Why cells ?
<p>

<center>
<table border=5 cellpadding=10>
<tr>
<td align=center><b>Advantage</b>
<td> Reduce the queuing delay for high priority traffic
</tr>
<tr>
<td align=center><b>Disadvantage</b>
<td> Overhead because of fragmentation and reassembly
</tr>
</table>
</center>


</h2>
